And I was listening for guitar trills and notes and things, and my sons, bless their

9
00:00:39,280 --> 00:00:42,260
heart, they said, Dad, turn down your music.

10
00:00:43,020 --> 00:00:47,290
I knew.

11
00:00:47,630 --> 00:00:48,830
I've still got it.

12
00:00:48,910 --> 00:00:49,950
I'm still with it.

13
00:00:52,740 --> 00:00:54,000
My music was too loud.

14
00:00:55,070 --> 00:00:55,430
Wow.

15
00:00:57,160 --> 00:01:03,000
In all seriousness this morning, I do want to say a note to those who were, and it's

16
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:06,940
a very awkward transition, I realize it, but I also want to say to those of you that are

17
00:01:06,940 --> 00:01:08,580
survivors of Pearl Harbor.

18
00:01:09,560 --> 00:01:10,760
62 years ago,

19
00:01:11,020 --> 00:01:12,940
many of you, some of you were there, some of you

20
00:01:12,940 --> 00:01:14,960
have family members that were there, and we

21
00:01:14,960 --> 00:01:17,020
just want to say again, thank you and God

22
00:01:17,020 --> 00:01:18,960
bless you for your service, and we

23
00:01:18,960 --> 00:01:19,840
remember you today.

24
00:01:22,550 --> 00:01:25,060
George Harrison, the Beatles,

25
00:01:25,400 --> 00:01:26,100
if you recall him,

26
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:29,180
he died two years ago on December 1st

27
00:01:29,180 --> 00:01:30,020
of 2001.

28
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:33,680
And there was a reporter from Rolling Stone magazine

29
00:01:33,680 --> 00:01:35,440
that quoted him as saying,

30
00:01:36,410 --> 00:01:37,850
everything else in

31
00:01:37,850 --> 00:01:39,190
life can wait.

32
00:01:39,790 --> 00:01:43,070
But the search for God cannot wait.

33
00:01:45,360 --> 00:01:50,280
That's an ex-Beatle saying that everything else in life can wait,

34
00:01:50,580 --> 00:01:53,680
but the search for God cannot wait.

35
00:01:54,870 --> 00:01:55,450
It's profound.

36
00:01:56,250 --> 00:02:01,890
I don't know if he ever found the Lord, but I know what he said is true.

37
00:02:03,340 --> 00:02:06,700
The search for God is the most important thing in life on earth.

38
00:02:08,230 --> 00:02:10,810
It is the all-important quest.

39
00:02:10,810 --> 00:02:21,880
And the end of the year, of course, is a traditional time to reflect on our relationships, our spiritual journey, our engagement with things eternal.

40
00:02:23,210 --> 00:02:30,450
No matter what kind of faith people have, the end of the year seems to bring about an openness to spiritual things.

41
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:41,380
And the first Sunday in Advent we had last week, we celebrated that vigilant waiting for the birth of Christ, signified by the candle of hope.

42
00:02:41,380 --> 00:02:51,420
And this morning, the second Sunday in Advent, represents our personal preparation for the birth of Christ, signified by the candle of peace.

43
00:02:53,400 --> 00:03:03,700
My friends, our quest for God and God's quest for us is what the birth of Christ and Christmas is all about.

44
00:03:04,880 --> 00:03:07,760
It's about God's quest for us.

45
00:03:07,760 --> 00:03:12,870
from Matthew chapter 3.

46
00:03:15,110 --> 00:03:18,110
In those days, John the Baptist came,

47
00:03:18,790 --> 00:03:21,330
preaching in the desert of Judea and saying,

48
00:03:21,910 --> 00:03:25,310
Repent, for the kingdom of heaven is near.

49
00:03:26,610 --> 00:03:29,890
This is he who was spoken of through the prophet Isaiah,

50
00:03:29,890 --> 00:03:32,870
a voice of one calling in the desert,

51
00:03:33,430 --> 00:03:35,510
Prepare the way for the Lord.

52
00:03:36,390 --> 00:03:38,170
Make straight paths for him.

53
00:03:39,980 --> 00:03:42,680
Now John's clothes were made of camel's hair,

54
00:03:42,680 --> 00:03:44,820
and he had a leather belt around his waist.

55
00:03:45,440 --> 00:03:47,740
His food was locusts and wild honey.

56
00:03:48,460 --> 00:03:51,820
And people went out to him from Jerusalem and all Judea

57
00:03:51,820 --> 00:03:56,240
and the whole region of the Jordan, confessing their sins.

58
00:03:56,800 --> 00:03:59,080
They were baptized by him in the Jordan River.

59
00:04:00,690 --> 00:04:03,490
But when he saw many of the Pharisees and the Sadducees

60
00:04:03,490 --> 00:04:06,470
coming to where he was baptizing, he said to them,

61
00:04:06,470 --> 00:04:11,890
You brood of vipers, who warned you to flee from the coming wrath?

62
00:04:12,660 --> 00:04:15,400
Produce fruit in keeping with repentance.

63
00:04:16,580 --> 00:04:18,580
And do not think you can say to yourselves,

64
00:04:18,960 --> 00:04:21,080
we have Abraham as our father.

65
00:04:21,880 --> 00:04:23,940
I tell you that out of these stones,

66
00:04:24,100 --> 00:04:26,320
God will raise up children for Abraham.

67
00:04:27,230 --> 00:04:29,090
The good fruit, the ax rather,

68
00:04:29,150 --> 00:04:30,950
is already at the root of the trees

69
00:04:30,950 --> 00:04:33,630
and every tree that does not produce good fruit

70
00:04:33,630 --> 00:04:36,290
will be cut down and thrown into the fire.

71
00:04:37,630 --> 00:04:40,610
I baptize you with water for repentance,

72
00:04:40,610 --> 00:04:47,050
But after me will come one who is more powerful than I, whose sandals I am not fit to carry.

73
00:04:47,610 --> 00:04:51,430
He will baptize you with the Holy Spirit and with fire.

74
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:57,160
His winnowing fork is in his hand, and he will clear the threshing floor,

75
00:04:57,560 --> 00:05:03,180
gathering his wheat into the barn and burning up the chaff with unquenchable fire.

76
00:05:07,250 --> 00:05:10,450
God broke the silence.

77
00:05:13,060 --> 00:05:17,600
When John the Baptist spoke, God broke the silence.

78
00:05:19,310 --> 00:05:26,570
That period of time between the Old Testament and the New Testament was a spiritually dark time.

79
00:05:28,460 --> 00:05:30,440
God, it seemed, had been silent.

80
00:05:31,820 --> 00:05:37,380
Prophecy had led people to expect a Messiah, but still they waited.

81
00:05:38,350 --> 00:05:41,270
And despite that dark spiritual tone of the land,

82
00:05:41,270 --> 00:05:47,590
There were those who were eagerly waiting, please come Messiah, please come.

83
00:05:49,300 --> 00:05:56,960
And then a man came, resembling the prophet Elijah, resembling him in manner and in dress.

84
00:05:57,200 --> 00:06:00,940
His cry was from God, a voice out of the silence.

85
00:06:01,720 --> 00:06:03,900
And his message was strong.

86
00:06:05,770 --> 00:06:08,880
Let's face it, his breath was probably strong.

87
00:06:10,750 --> 00:06:13,500
His dress code made a statement.

88
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:17,080
This man you could not ignore.

89
00:06:19,170 --> 00:06:25,550
A voice that came not from the city, the place of the people and the hustle and the bustle.

90
00:06:25,550 --> 00:06:33,150
No, the voice came from the desert, from the wilderness, from the place of quiet, a place of loneliness.

91
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:39,580
A place where people became open to the things of God.

92
00:06:41,190 --> 00:06:43,760
And there, a voice cried out.

93
00:06:43,760 --> 00:06:50,940
The wilderness was not only a place that symbolized an openness to God.

94
00:06:51,900 --> 00:06:57,180
Israel had also disobeyed God in the wilderness in generations past.

95
00:06:58,120 --> 00:07:02,120
And there they had found judgment and God's mercy.

96
00:07:03,990 --> 00:07:10,150
And so it was startling that God would break the silence and speak from the desert.

97
00:07:12,010 --> 00:07:12,970
And the people came.

98
00:07:12,970 --> 00:07:16,070
They came from all classes, all stripes.

99
00:07:16,070 --> 00:07:23,350
They came to see the spectacle in the desert, to see the scruffy man that looked like Elijah,

100
00:07:24,030 --> 00:07:29,650
who ate meals off the land, who resembled the very poorest of the poor.

101
00:07:31,640 --> 00:07:33,920
And through that man, the silence was broken.

102
00:07:35,780 --> 00:07:41,260
Well, this event, this breaking of the silence had been prophesied hundreds of years before

103
00:07:41,260 --> 00:07:47,220
in Isaiah chapter 40, comfort, comfort my people, says your God.

104
00:07:47,220 --> 00:07:50,200
speak tenderly to Jerusalem

105
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:51,560
and proclaim to her

106
00:07:51,560 --> 00:07:54,280
that her hard service has been completed

107
00:07:54,280 --> 00:07:57,020
that her sin has been paid for

108
00:07:57,020 --> 00:08:00,020
that she has received from the Lord's hand

109
00:08:00,020 --> 00:08:02,360
double for all her sins

110
00:08:02,360 --> 00:08:04,740
a voice of one calling

111
00:08:04,740 --> 00:08:07,460
in the desert prepare the way for the Lord

112
00:08:07,460 --> 00:08:11,000
make straight in the wilderness a highway for our God

113
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:14,040
every valley shall be raised up

114
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:16,460
every mountain and hill made low

115
00:08:17,440 --> 00:08:21,860
The rough ground shall become level, the rugged places a plain.

116
00:08:22,700 --> 00:08:29,380
And the glory of the Lord will be revealed, and all mankind together will see it.

117
00:08:29,380 --> 00:08:33,330
For the mouth of the Lord has spoken.

118
00:08:34,460 --> 00:08:35,880
Isaiah chapter 40.

119
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:41,920
And now this text comes alive in John the Baptist.

120
00:08:42,160 --> 00:08:44,120
God has broken the silence.

121
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:47,280
God is speaking again.

122
00:08:49,740 --> 00:08:51,280
And the message is this.

123
00:08:52,060 --> 00:08:56,320
Repent, for the kingdom of heaven is near.

124
00:08:59,240 --> 00:09:00,520
The kingdom of heaven is near.

125
00:09:00,640 --> 00:09:02,440
What does that mean?

126
00:09:03,720 --> 00:09:08,840
The kingdom of heaven is a phrase that expresses that God's rule has begun.

127
00:09:09,560 --> 00:09:13,220
It's a phrase that says God is doing something.

128
00:09:13,220 --> 00:09:20,300
When Jesus comes, God in the flesh, the kingdom of God has come on earth.

129
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:27,040
And when Jesus comes again, the kingdom of God will finally be consummated.

130
00:09:28,130 --> 00:09:29,930
And now the kingdom is drawing near.

131
00:09:30,610 --> 00:09:32,190
The baby is about to come.

132
00:09:33,160 --> 00:09:36,160
The message is get ready and repent.

133
00:09:39,220 --> 00:09:42,030
Repentance is a great word.

134
00:09:42,030 --> 00:09:51,150
It means literally, in the biblical sense, to change one's mind, to go a different direction.

135
00:09:52,190 --> 00:10:02,110
It's a decision, not only to decide to do something different, but an action, backed up by a resolve, to really do something different.

136
00:10:03,850 --> 00:10:08,690
It's a radical notion, because it means more than just a deviation from course.

137
00:10:08,690 --> 00:10:14,330
It means 180 degrees about face kind of direction change.

138
00:10:17,560 --> 00:10:20,060
Another has simply described repentance this way.

139
00:10:21,860 --> 00:10:29,520
It's simply to stop running after everything else and see that God is pursuing us.

140
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:38,260
It's to make decisions for God in our daily life that shows where our hope really lies.

141
00:10:39,980 --> 00:10:42,800
It's turning into the face of God.

142
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:48,720
it's a funny word repentance today we don't hear it much

143
00:10:48,720 --> 00:10:52,780
I think we're numb to the idea of repentance

144
00:10:52,780 --> 00:10:57,580
because our world doesn't conceive that anything is really wrong

145
00:10:57,580 --> 00:11:01,440
there's really nothing to repent from

146
00:11:01,440 --> 00:11:05,840
because nothing is actually wrong

147
00:11:05,840 --> 00:11:09,000
whatever one thinks they're the harbiter

148
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:11,320
and the determiner of morality

149
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:13,850
and it doesn't matter what you do

150
00:11:13,850 --> 00:11:18,320
and so we don't hear the word repentance much in our culture

151
00:11:21,410 --> 00:11:24,310
But John says still and speaks to us, he says, repent.

152
00:11:25,230 --> 00:11:27,030
Get ready for the coming of the Lord.

153
00:11:29,220 --> 00:11:34,650
Notice he was talking first to the Jewish people, the chosen people.

154
00:11:35,210 --> 00:11:42,740
People that were sure that by their practices and their lineage that they were right with God.

155
00:11:42,860 --> 00:11:44,740
They had the right credentials.

156
00:11:45,660 --> 00:11:47,280
They had the right pedigree.

157
00:11:49,940 --> 00:11:51,760
There was a TV show called MASH.

158
00:11:51,860 --> 00:11:53,100
Many of you remember this one.

159
00:11:53,100 --> 00:12:06,920
And Dr. Charles Emerson Winchester III made it clear what separated him from everybody else was this quote,

160
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:08,900
I'm a Winchester.

161
00:12:09,480 --> 00:12:13,280
I can't do the accent, but you know the phrase.

162
00:12:14,120 --> 00:12:18,880
He was a Winchester and everybody else was not.

163
00:12:19,920 --> 00:12:22,180
And that's why he was superior.

164
00:12:23,770 --> 00:12:24,670
He was a Winchester.

165
00:12:25,910 --> 00:12:31,630
For him, the family name, his pedigree, separated him from everybody else.

166
00:12:31,790 --> 00:12:32,710
And he let you know it.

167
00:12:35,140 --> 00:12:37,100
Other people carry other burdens similarly.

168
00:12:39,070 --> 00:12:45,940
One woman received her education at Harvard and found a way to work Harvard into every conversation.

169
00:12:47,470 --> 00:12:48,810
You've met those types.

170
00:12:50,880 --> 00:12:57,140
That idea, that kind of spirit, that kind of heart is what John the Baptist is dealing with.

171
00:12:57,940 --> 00:12:59,820
He's challenging these people.

172
00:13:00,850 --> 00:13:04,750
It doesn't matter what lineage you come from, what family you come from,

173
00:13:04,890 --> 00:13:08,930
what university you graduated from, what credentials you hold.

174
00:13:09,330 --> 00:13:11,510
Repent, for the kingdom of heaven is near.

175
00:13:14,360 --> 00:13:21,780
You see, coming from the right family doesn't necessarily produce life change that honors God.

176
00:13:26,170 --> 00:13:27,870
And so John said to these people, repent.

177
00:13:30,040 --> 00:13:35,380
Friends, I want us to know that God's purposes are not just restricted to the Israelites.

178
00:13:35,380 --> 00:13:46,360
Because God is interested in the people of all nations, all colors, all backgrounds, all classes, all people.

179
00:13:46,520 --> 00:13:49,290
Jesus came for everyone.

180
00:13:51,680 --> 00:13:56,660
And it blows the mind of the Israelite who has the right pedigree.

181
00:13:58,820 --> 00:14:02,160
And John's preaching extends to all the people.

182
00:14:02,160 --> 00:14:05,000
It puts them all on the level playing field.

183
00:14:05,400 --> 00:14:09,240
To enter the kingdom of God, we must repent, all of us,

184
00:14:10,090 --> 00:14:14,830
and ultimately accept Jesus Christ, who he is and what he's done.

185
00:14:18,330 --> 00:14:22,730
In the midst of John's preaching, he then points to Jesus,

186
00:14:23,650 --> 00:14:26,250
the fulfillment of this prophecy from Isaiah.

187
00:14:27,190 --> 00:14:32,140
And John declares that Jesus of Nazareth is God.

188
00:14:32,560 --> 00:14:39,480
Friends, to find God, we have to seek Jesus.

189
00:14:42,370 --> 00:14:46,730
And no matter whether you go to church or go to the right places of worship

190
00:14:46,730 --> 00:14:50,850
or listen to the right radio programs or watch the right television preachers

191
00:14:50,850 --> 00:14:56,720
or try and do all the right things, it's all about Jesus.

192
00:14:58,200 --> 00:14:59,440
It's only about Jesus.

193
00:15:01,120 --> 00:15:09,850
And real peace and real fulfillment and real wholeness comes only in the person and the work of Jesus Christ.

194
00:15:13,770 --> 00:15:22,280
The man from the little town of Bethlehem, the one to whom John the Baptist points, is

195
00:15:22,280 --> 00:15:23,240
God in the flesh.

196
00:15:24,770 --> 00:15:29,390
God in the flesh come to baptize his followers in the power of the Holy Spirit.

197
00:15:31,130 --> 00:15:37,710
What we see here is John's preaching and baptizing, anticipating the preaching and the baptizing

198
00:15:37,710 --> 00:15:39,630
activity of Jesus the Christ.

199
00:15:42,780 --> 00:15:47,060
And then John talks about Jesus' winnowing fork.

200
00:15:49,480 --> 00:15:56,520
As one who was raised in the suburbs, I don't know anything about farming or farming instruments.

201
00:15:56,520 --> 00:15:58,340
And I suspect many of us don't either.

202
00:15:59,740 --> 00:16:01,640
What is a winnowing fork?

203
00:16:03,280 --> 00:16:05,560
A winnowing fork was a farm tool.

204
00:16:06,660 --> 00:16:09,200
I imagine it looking something like a pitchfork.

205
00:16:10,610 --> 00:16:15,230
Designed to do one thing, to throw the trampled wheat up into the air.

206
00:16:15,230 --> 00:16:20,790
whereby the wind begins to separate the good grain as it falls to earth

207
00:16:20,790 --> 00:16:23,570
and separates it from the light what they call chaff

208
00:16:23,570 --> 00:16:27,890
which is the refuse part of the trampled grain as it blows away in the air.

209
00:16:28,970 --> 00:16:31,050
And as you throw the wheat up into the air

210
00:16:31,050 --> 00:16:34,760
the grains fall and the chaff is blown away.

211
00:16:36,170 --> 00:16:41,190
And that's the word picture that Jesus uses in this agrarian society

212
00:16:41,190 --> 00:16:43,270
as they spoke to their hearts and said

213
00:16:44,090 --> 00:16:48,190
God is going to separate people who truly know Jesus,

214
00:16:48,930 --> 00:16:51,530
who truly are of the kingdom from those who are not.

215
00:16:54,020 --> 00:16:57,980
And the question he's asking is whose side are you on?

216
00:16:59,720 --> 00:17:00,480
Who do you follow?

217
00:17:01,740 --> 00:17:02,880
Who really fills your heart?

218
00:17:06,040 --> 00:17:10,550
And so the challenge becomes we must break our silence.

219
00:17:15,460 --> 00:17:18,500
There was a professor at the University of Pennsylvania Law School

220
00:17:18,500 --> 00:17:23,160
that for more than 20 years, every year as he began his sessions in September,

221
00:17:23,540 --> 00:17:27,450
He would start the first class like this.

222
00:17:28,480 --> 00:17:30,480
He would go to the blackboard, take a piece of chalk,

223
00:17:31,180 --> 00:17:34,520
and he drew two numbers, a two and a four.

224
00:17:36,260 --> 00:17:39,040
And he asked the class, what's the solution?

225
00:17:41,630 --> 00:17:44,210
And invariably one student would shout out six,

226
00:17:45,330 --> 00:17:47,030
and somebody else would shout out two,

227
00:17:48,180 --> 00:17:49,840
and somebody else would shout out eight.

228
00:17:52,180 --> 00:17:53,180
And he would shake his head.

229
00:17:53,440 --> 00:17:55,460
Every year he would shake his head.

230
00:17:55,460 --> 00:17:59,600
And he said this year after year, ladies and gentlemen,

231
00:18:00,540 --> 00:18:05,900
Unless you know what the problem is, you cannot possibly find the answer.

232
00:18:07,970 --> 00:18:10,410
I have not given you yet the problem.

233
00:18:13,640 --> 00:18:16,560
Friends, in seeking to prepare for the coming of Jesus,

234
00:18:17,560 --> 00:18:22,960
in seeking to truly have our hearts molded into the conformity of the character of Christ,

235
00:18:22,960 --> 00:18:26,220
to truly repent and to be open to the things of God,

236
00:18:26,400 --> 00:18:28,860
we need to know what the problem is.

237
00:18:28,860 --> 00:18:39,600
you cannot go ramshackle into repentance until we know what the problem is and the problem friends

238
00:18:39,600 --> 00:18:51,700
is us the problem is we desire as the scriptures say to do our own things and to go our own way

239
00:18:51,700 --> 00:19:04,380
and we need sometimes to reflect and say lord i know you but sometimes i still meander i don't

240
00:19:04,380 --> 00:19:11,140
trust. I don't follow. Sometimes I don't believe you're going to come through in the pinch and I

241
00:19:11,140 --> 00:19:20,960
lose faith. Whatever your experience, you need to know what the problem is. Some of you this morning

242
00:19:20,960 --> 00:19:30,900
are hurting deep down inside. You may not even realize it consciously, but when you begin to

243
00:19:30,900 --> 00:19:36,440
process the things I'm going to say in the next few moments, I think you'll realize it's true.

244
00:19:36,440 --> 00:19:42,300
I spoke to a good friend of mine yesterday, my friend Jeff, psychologist.

245
00:19:43,420 --> 00:19:47,640
We shared our hearts and spent a few moments, and a comment he said again is so true.

246
00:19:48,620 --> 00:19:50,680
We're broken people leading broken people.

247
00:19:52,150 --> 00:19:53,510
And that's really the human condition.

248
00:19:55,180 --> 00:19:57,740
All of us have our hurts, our pains, our struggles.

249
00:19:57,960 --> 00:19:59,900
We're all imperfect before God.

250
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:01,500
All of us need a Savior.

251
00:20:02,340 --> 00:20:05,000
We're broken people leading other broken people.

252
00:20:07,780 --> 00:20:12,420
It's when we get honest about that that life really takes on real meaning and real purpose.

253
00:20:15,310 --> 00:20:23,940
Some of you this morning are hurting about events that have happened in this church both recently and years ago.

254
00:20:26,300 --> 00:20:31,220
People have offended you or leaders have offended or hurt you.

255
00:20:32,170 --> 00:20:35,030
Politics in the church has been brutal at times to you.

256
00:20:35,390 --> 00:20:41,010
And the result can be anger and mistrust or fear, whatever it is.

257
00:20:42,880 --> 00:20:46,920
Friends, sometimes we may be living and doing all the right things,

258
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:50,860
but deep down we're harboring anger towards others and pain and frustration.

259
00:20:51,660 --> 00:20:57,900
And sometimes we just have to give it up to the Lord and confess those things.

260
00:20:58,000 --> 00:20:59,660
Let God heal those things.

261
00:21:03,130 --> 00:21:08,070
Friends, unresolved hurts and pains in the life of believers that are buried down deep,

262
00:21:09,280 --> 00:21:11,400
they can affect how we relate to each other.

263
00:21:11,820 --> 00:21:15,800
We carry those around and we make commitments in our soul

264
00:21:15,800 --> 00:21:18,000
that we're never going to get hurt again.

265
00:21:18,960 --> 00:21:22,240
And so we don't let anybody else really touch our soul.

266
00:21:23,820 --> 00:21:26,980
Because when somebody touches our soul, we can get hurt.

267
00:21:28,640 --> 00:21:32,080
And so we commit to putting up barriers and walls and always being fine

268
00:21:32,080 --> 00:21:39,200
and never letting anybody really touch those places in our souls

269
00:21:39,200 --> 00:21:44,740
that Jesus wants to mold and to shape and to grow and to heal.

270
00:21:48,010 --> 00:21:53,510
Some of you this morning are hurting from issues in your families in which you grew up.

271
00:21:57,120 --> 00:22:02,240
And if I was to just begin to take a poll, we could all share various stories.

272
00:22:03,880 --> 00:22:05,320
Some didn't get the love you deserved.

273
00:22:06,560 --> 00:22:10,080
Some had parents unstable, destructive to you emotionally.

274
00:22:10,880 --> 00:22:14,100
Some just put incredible amounts of pressure upon you.

275
00:22:15,020 --> 00:22:19,600
And to deal with all of that, you've created patterns of relating to others that keep people at a distance.

276
00:22:19,600 --> 00:22:24,480
You're not going to let people that are supposed to love you get close enough because they always hurt you.

277
00:22:26,090 --> 00:22:30,430
So you put up walls and we stay distant from each other.

278
00:22:31,440 --> 00:22:41,390
And the reason I bring that up, friends, is that our commitment to protecting ourselves like that is sin.

279
00:22:42,470 --> 00:22:47,930
Because Jesus calls us to love each other as he has loved us.

280
00:22:48,410 --> 00:22:52,670
And we really can't love each other from behind walls, can we?

281
00:22:54,320 --> 00:22:58,100
When we're defended, we can't actually let somebody's soul touch ours,

282
00:22:58,220 --> 00:23:02,260
and we can't touch somebody else's soul because the walls are too high.

283
00:23:05,690 --> 00:23:10,030
And so I'm speaking to a congregation I know that you don't run around

284
00:23:10,030 --> 00:23:11,830
and do crazy things in the middle of the night,

285
00:23:11,910 --> 00:23:15,770
and I know that you are a good, upstanding congregation of people.

286
00:23:15,770 --> 00:23:21,170
You don't race your cars too fast, and you don't drink and drive,

287
00:23:21,430 --> 00:23:24,710
and you don't beat up your friends, and I know all this.

288
00:23:24,710 --> 00:23:29,610
But, you know, deep down we can still have sin in our hearts that's not seen outside.

289
00:23:31,020 --> 00:23:33,260
It's these emotional, relational things.

290
00:23:33,440 --> 00:23:34,380
We protect ourselves.

291
00:23:34,500 --> 00:23:36,820
We don't really let anybody touch us.

292
00:23:36,880 --> 00:23:38,500
We don't really touch anybody else.

293
00:23:38,740 --> 00:23:40,460
We really don't lead or encourage.

294
00:23:40,740 --> 00:23:48,200
We just kind of go through life bouncing off each other gently, innocuously, pleasantly.

295
00:23:50,960 --> 00:23:52,800
But, friends, God calls us to so much deeper.

296
00:23:52,800 --> 00:23:58,930
and some this morning you were sitting there

297
00:23:58,930 --> 00:24:02,620
and though on the outside things look fine

298
00:24:02,620 --> 00:24:07,030
there are issues of oppression and addictions and struggles

299
00:24:07,030 --> 00:24:09,990
deep inside your soul you don't want anybody to know about

300
00:24:09,990 --> 00:24:15,320
and I'm just here to say that I believe that God wants us

301
00:24:15,320 --> 00:24:19,260
as we leave 2003, as we move into 2004

302
00:24:19,260 --> 00:24:23,760
I believe that God wants us to rise to new places in health

303
00:24:23,760 --> 00:24:26,540
as individuals before God

304
00:24:26,540 --> 00:24:32,930
and to begin to be whole and let the Spirit of God minister to those broken places

305
00:24:32,930 --> 00:24:36,490
that we've never let Him deal with at all.

306
00:24:36,490 --> 00:24:43,600
Because we desire to be an authentic, real church community

307
00:24:43,600 --> 00:24:47,460
with real relationships and real church family.

308
00:24:47,860 --> 00:24:52,100
Relationships that grow us into the character of Jesus the Christ.

309
00:24:57,170 --> 00:25:00,670
I'm excited this past year, years actually,

310
00:25:00,670 --> 00:25:04,110
for developing and crystallizing our mission,

311
00:25:06,060 --> 00:25:09,400
for beginning to bring together a structure

312
00:25:09,400 --> 00:25:11,540
that helps us to do ministry

313
00:25:11,540 --> 00:25:14,880
in a way that's responsive to needs more quickly.

314
00:25:15,740 --> 00:25:18,400
We're getting healthy in our structure and our mission,

315
00:25:18,520 --> 00:25:19,800
and now we need to bring health

316
00:25:19,800 --> 00:25:22,120
to our very spirits and our souls.

317
00:25:26,870 --> 00:25:30,420
This candle this morning is the candle of peace.

318
00:25:32,820 --> 00:25:35,940
Jesus the Christ brings us peace

319
00:25:35,940 --> 00:25:40,770
with God and with others around you

320
00:25:40,770 --> 00:25:42,960
and with ourselves.

321
00:25:45,160 --> 00:25:47,740
Jesus brings peace between us and God

322
00:25:47,740 --> 00:25:50,500
with each other and within ourselves.

323
00:25:52,910 --> 00:25:55,170
And some of you may not sense that peace

324
00:25:55,170 --> 00:25:56,770
with him this morning.

325
00:25:58,040 --> 00:26:00,300
You may not sense peace with others.

326
00:26:02,480 --> 00:26:04,900
And you may not sense peace in yourself.

327
00:26:08,650 --> 00:26:09,890
God broke the silence

328
00:26:09,890 --> 00:26:13,780
by having John the Baptist speak in the desert,

329
00:26:13,780 --> 00:26:18,920
in the place that represented an openness to the things of God.

330
00:26:21,720 --> 00:26:25,060
And encouragement this morning is for us to break our silence

331
00:26:25,060 --> 00:26:30,700
by letting God, letting the Holy Spirit come and touch the very deepest places

332
00:26:30,700 --> 00:26:35,020
and begin a process of healing that we might be open and free

333
00:26:35,020 --> 00:26:38,700
for the filling of the Spirit and the leading in our lives.

334
00:26:40,300 --> 00:26:46,460
I want us to be the most filled up, Spirit-led, overflowingly gracious

335
00:26:46,460 --> 00:26:50,680
and whole congregation anywhere in North Orange County

336
00:26:50,680 --> 00:26:53,100
because we're open to the things of God.

337
00:26:58,430 --> 00:27:00,270
So in a few moments, we're going to have an opportunity,

338
00:27:00,630 --> 00:27:02,890
a time of worship and singing and of prayer.

339
00:27:06,200 --> 00:27:11,480
And if you would be so bold and honest to come and receive prayer for healing,

340
00:27:12,020 --> 00:27:15,120
for inner healing, for spiritual healing, for emotional healing,

341
00:27:15,380 --> 00:27:17,260
for whatever it is, to begin to say,

342
00:27:17,260 --> 00:27:22,840
Lord, I want to go into 2004 in a process of God stirring and healing

343
00:27:22,840 --> 00:27:25,530
my soul that I'm going to invite you

344
00:27:25,530 --> 00:27:27,500
to come. Our prayer team

345
00:27:27,500 --> 00:27:29,360
will be here. This

346
00:27:29,360 --> 00:27:31,660
is Advent. This is the preparation

347
00:27:31,660 --> 00:27:33,500
for the coming of the

348
00:27:33,500 --> 00:27:35,770
Lord. Let us not

349
00:27:35,770 --> 00:27:37,730
hold on to things that hold us back

350
00:27:37,730 --> 00:27:39,810
from real peace with Him, with

351
00:27:39,810 --> 00:27:41,310
others, and with ourselves.

352
00:27:44,530 --> 00:27:46,190
And others, I'm going to invite you to come

353
00:27:46,190 --> 00:27:48,690
this morning. As John

354
00:27:48,690 --> 00:27:50,210
Wimber wrote in that song

355
00:27:50,210 --> 00:27:52,630
that I really enjoy and many of you do as well

356
00:27:52,630 --> 00:27:54,630
called More Love and More

357
00:27:54,630 --> 00:27:56,610
power. Perhaps you

358
00:27:56,610 --> 00:27:58,690
just want more of God this

359
00:27:58,690 --> 00:28:00,710
morning. You just want more of

360
00:28:00,710 --> 00:28:02,730
His power and His love in your life.

361
00:28:03,810 --> 00:28:04,650
Then you come and

362
00:28:04,650 --> 00:28:05,750
receive prayer as well.

363
00:28:06,580 --> 00:28:08,540
And we're going to pray the filling of the Holy Spirit

364
00:28:08,540 --> 00:28:10,740
to fill you up and spill

365
00:28:10,740 --> 00:28:13,700
right over the top that you

366
00:28:13,700 --> 00:28:14,660
might be a witness

367
00:28:14,660 --> 00:28:18,760
in Samaria and Judea and

368
00:28:18,760 --> 00:28:22,640
the rest of the world. So if you want

369
00:28:22,640 --> 00:28:23,940
more love and more power,

370
00:28:25,950 --> 00:28:28,410
if you want healing, if you want

371
00:28:28,410 --> 00:28:37,430
God's hand in your life, this morning is the time. This morning is the time. Friends, healing

372
00:28:37,430 --> 00:28:44,470
doesn't happen overnight. It can, but not often. It can happen in stages, but it needs

373
00:28:44,470 --> 00:28:54,800
to begin somewhere. We want us to go free into next year, to go into our final celebration

374
00:28:54,800 --> 00:29:00,020
of the birth of the Lord, free to receive all that God wants to pour into your life,

375
00:29:00,020 --> 00:29:04,560
ready to be used of God

376
00:29:04,560 --> 00:29:06,020
in total freedom

377
00:29:06,020 --> 00:29:09,910
the worship team is coming

378
00:29:09,910 --> 00:29:14,230
we're going to be singing and meditating on these

379
00:29:14,230 --> 00:29:16,400
ideas, the prayer team

380
00:29:16,400 --> 00:29:19,450
is coming, in the bulletin we've

381
00:29:19,450 --> 00:29:21,350
labeled this time, worship and ministry

382
00:29:21,350 --> 00:29:24,210
because it's a time for us to

383
00:29:24,210 --> 00:29:26,090
receive and give to the Lord

384
00:29:26,090 --> 00:29:27,150
he is the audience

385
00:29:27,150 --> 00:29:29,310
we want to give him our lives

386
00:29:29,310 --> 00:29:31,280
all of us

387
00:29:31,280 --> 00:29:34,770
allow his spirit to meet us there

